  "merger_description": "Space Exploration Technologies Corp. (**SpaceX**), through its subsidiary, proposes to acquire 100% of the shares in Anysphere, Inc. (**Anysphere**).\n\nSpaceX is the ultimate parent company of the SpaceX group, which includes X.AI Corp (**xAI**), an artificial intelligence (**AI**) company, and X Corp., which owns and operates the X social media platform (formerly Twitter). xAI develops the Grok family of large language models and offers Grok Build, a terminal-native AI coding tool, to Grok and X subscribers. Grok Build currently runs on xAI\u2019s Grok model family.\n\nAnysphere develops and operates Cursor, an AI coding tool used by software developers to write and review code with the assistance of AI models. Cursor users can select from a range of third-party large language models (including Grok models) or Anysphere\u2019s proprietary Composer model to power the platform\u2019s AI assistant features. Composer is purpose-built for Cursor and is not offered as a standalone general-purpose model for other purposes.",
